Package: cier
Title: Detect Careless and Insufficient Effort Responding in Survey Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Markus", "Steiner", , "markus.d.steiner@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: A lean, fast toolkit for detecting careless and insufficient
    effort responding ('C/IER') in survey data using indirect
    response-pattern indices (longstring, intra-individual response
    variability, personal reliability, psychometric synonyms and antonyms,
    Mahalanobis distance, person-total correlation, nonparametric
    person-fit statistics, and the sequence indices autocorrelation and
    'Laz.R'), following the indirect-index battery evaluated by Goldammer
    et al. (2024) <doi:10.3758/s13428-024-02484-3>, plus survey-timing
    indices (total and per-page completion time) and a direct
    attention-check index. Flags respondents through an auditable,
    false-positive-rate-controlled layer with transparent, citable
    defaults.
